&lt;p&gt;Deputy Sister / Charge Nurse Lulworth Ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to take your nursing career to the next level, Lulworth Ward has a new Band 6 Deputy Sister / Charge Nurse Posts available within Older People&#39;s Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From elderly care, this role provide real career progression for ambitious Band 5 nurses, looking for their next challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to work and develop in a supportive working environment at a hospital that 90 per cent of its staff would recommend to their friends and family, and rated ‘good’ by its regulator, contact us to find out more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personalised training and development plans, including access to our university-recognised Leading Safe and Effective Quality Patient Care programme, will see you rapidly develop your skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your ethos is one of continuous improvement, and are driven to provide compassionate, open, respectful, accountable and safe care every day, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible working opportunities, including rotational posts, are available, as well as support with relocation costs, where appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 19/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date week commencing: 07/12/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jay Davidson (Ward Lead) - jay.davidson@poole.nhs.uk / 0300 019 8296 / 0300 019 8294&lt;/p&gt;
